Willy Paul has received his YouTube Gold Creator award, popularly known as the Golden Plaque. The award is given to users who cross the one million subscribers mark. He thanked fans on Instagram for enabling him to achieve the new milestone. "Thank you all for the love and support,‚Äù Willy Paul wrote. "And to that blogger who had doubts about my numbers, next time, just ask me politely and I'll answer you. One love. GOLD." Willy Paul also told off haters who said his numbers were not legit. "We hit a million subscribers on YouTube. The reason I'm doing this video is that a while back, some people said my subscribers were fake," he said. "I'm Mr Organize, and it will stay like that." He has more than 211 million views and counting.